<item>
            <title>[SOLR-16747] Remove git requirement for gradle build</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16747</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the source release cannot be built with &lt;tt&gt;gradle assemble&lt;/tt&gt; or checked with &lt;tt&gt;gradle check&lt;/tt&gt; since the ref-guide tasks require the solr directory to be a git repository.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The easy way to fix this is to not include the ref-guide tasks if the root directory doesn&apos;t contain the &lt;tt&gt;.git/&lt;/tt&gt; directory.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
